Task 1: Understanding HTTP with curl
Subtask 1.1: Basic GET Requests
First, let's explore how web requests work using curl, a powerful command-line tool for making HTTP requests.

Step 1: Open a terminal and test your internet connection

ping -c 3 google.com
Step 2: Make your first GET request to a simple API

curl https://httpbin.org/get
This command sends a GET request to httpbin.org, a service designed for testing HTTP requests. You should see a JSON response containing information about your request.

Step 3: Make a GET request with verbose output to see the full HTTP conversation

curl -v https://httpbin.org/get
The -v flag shows you the complete HTTP headers and response details.

Step 4: Save the response to a file for later analysis

curl https://httpbin.org/get -o response.json
cat response.json
